<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-04-08</DATELINE><TITLE>Emergency response to the outbreak of COVID-19: the Korean case</TITLE><BODY>Abstract This letter aims to describe how Korea can improve its emergency response to the outbreak of COVID-19. The key finding is that the nation has to shift from a self-interest–oriented response to a shared-interest–oriented response. Similarly, neighboring nations could form a national framework of networks among stakeholders.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>